            "answer_text": "Scripts are used to write languages. There can be multiple languages sharing a script (i.e. written in the same script) and multiple scripts used for writing the same language. Coming to the question, Sanskrit these days primarily uses the devanagari script. However, it's also written in many of the other regional scripts of India and South East Asia. For e.g. in my family, my dad prefers to read Sanskrit shlokas written using the malayalam script but I prefer the devanagari script. I have a few relatives who use Sanskrit shloka books written in english script as well. Devanagari script is used for writing multiple languages like Hindi, Marathi, Nepali apart from Sanskrit. ",
